PART 4: CRASH ANALYSIS
==============================================================================

=== Assertion that fired ===

File:      /usr/include/c++/11/bits/stl_vector.h
Line:      1045
Condition: __n < this->size()
Context:   std::vector<_Tp, _Alloc>::operator[]

This is a BOUNDS-CHECKED vector operator[] (debug/hardened STL build).

=== Which vector? ===

The crash PC 0x7fa284 is the instruction immediately after the bl at 0x7fa280.
The bl at 0x7fa280 is reached from the branch at 0x7f9e40:

  7f9e3c: cmp x20, x0, asr #4    ; compare index with (tasks.end - tasks.begin) >> 4
  7f9e40: b.cs 7fa284             ; branch if index >= tasks.size() (UNSIGNED >=)

This is in the DISPATCH LOOP (first loop), checking tasks[x20] bounds.

=== The vector that crashed: tasks (std::vector<std::future<void>>) ===

From the assertion string at 0x1c67a88:
  "std::vector<_Tp, _Alloc>::operator[](std::vector<_Tp, _Alloc>::size_type)
   [with _Tp = std::future<void>; _Alloc = std::allocator<std::future<void> >;
    std::vector<_Tp, _Alloc>::reference = std::future<void>&;
    std::vector<_Tp, _Alloc>::size_type = long unsigned int]"

=== Register state at crash (compress_write frame) ===

x19 = 0x3c0ec90  : comp_file pointer (ds_compress_file_t*)
x20 = 1           : loop index (second iteration)
x23 = 0x81 = 129  : num_chunks (total chunks to process)
x25 = 0x800000    : data length = 8,388,608 bytes (8 MB)
x22 = 0x9038      : 36,920 = context element stride (sizeof(comp_thread_ctxt_t))

=== The mismatch ===

tasks vector:    129 elements (16 bytes each, 2064 total)
contexts vector: 923 elements (40 bytes each, 36920 total)

CRITICAL OBSERVATION: tasks has 129 elements, contexts has 923 elements.
These vectors should have the same number of elements!

The contexts vector has 923 = 129 * 7.15... This suggests the contexts vector
was resized multiple times by different concurrent calls while tasks was only
sized once. This is the race condition.

=== chunk_size computation ===

compress-chunk-size = 65534 (0xFFFE) -- user-specified, NOT 64KB-aligned
data_length = 8,388,608 (8 MB)
num_chunks = ceil(8388608 / 65534) = 129 (x23 = 0x81)

The chunk size 65534 is deliberately non-power-of-2 to trigger edge cases
in the buffer allocation and vector sizing logic.

